FOX'S TEEN SOAP OPERA 'TRIBES' WILL FADE OUT NEXT MONTH 
"Tribes," a 3-month-old TV soap opera aimed at teen-agers and young adults, has 
been canceled by Fox Television Stations Productions. It will have its final 
broadcast July 13 on KTTV Channel 11. 
The serial, also running on other Fox-owned stations, was developed with the 
intention of syndicating it nationally. 
